{"hits": {"hits": [{"created": "2026-04-20T18:51:04.126108+00:00", "modified": "2026-04-20T18:51:04.928877+00:00", "id": 19669181, "conceptrecid": "19669180", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.19669181", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.19669180", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19669181", "metadata": {"title": "A test of the metapopulation model of the species\u2013area relationship", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.19669181", "publication_date": "2002", "description": "(Uploaded by Plazi for the Bat Literature Project) Aim The species\u2013area relationship is a ubiquitous pattern. Previous methods describing the relationship have done little to elucidate mechanisms producing the pattern. Hanski &amp; Gyllenberg (Science, 1997, 275, 397) have shown that a model of metapopulation dynamics yields predictable species\u2013area relationships. We elaborate on the biological interpretation of this mechanistic model and test the prediction that communities of species with a higher risk of extinction caused by environmental stochasticity should have lower species\u2013area slopes than communities experiencing less impact of environmental stochasticity.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Matter, Stephen F.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hanski, Ilkka", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gyllenberg, Mats", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/8b43a35385b14bebaf5066ceaf20fe19", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/2258b2d34f225cb24d90c11a0e02d442c842c0500595b4967db0ed0a47409fef", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/IJBP68VZ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/IJBP68VZ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/c7f1cf81